Bring a large pan of @water{} to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1} then thinly slice widthways.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g} and stir-fry until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @British Pork Mince{240%g} to the mushrooms and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

> TIP: Drain off any excess fat if necessary.

Once the pan of water is boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{2} and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Set aside.

Stir the bok choy and garlic into the pork mince, stir-fry until just soft, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Teriyaki Sauce{150%ml} and @Water{50%ml}, ensuring everything is well coated.

Add the noodles to the teriyaki mixture. Stir together and cook until everything is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

> TIP: Add a splash more water if the noodles look a little dry.

Serve the noodles in #bowls{}.

Scatter the spring onion on top.

Enjoy!